Cincinnati Business Courier





In This Article






Manufacturing




Media & Marketing




Dennis Wells




Jeff Croskey




Shawn Toney




John Bagwell




David McCauley






 


 















 Enlarge





                Jeff Croskey has been named president of LSI’s graphics segment.            

                Provided            






LSI Industries Inc. has a new leader for its graphics segment.
Jeff Croskey has been named president of LSI’s (Nasdaq: LYTS) graphics segment.











 Enlarge





                Jeff Croskey has been named president of LSI’s graphics segment.            
Provided






 


Croskey has an extensive background in the signage and graphics industry and most recently served as vice president of Creative Sign Designs in Tampa, Fla. He previously worked at Image International Corp., McNichols Co. and Goodyear Tire & Rubber Co.
Croskey received an MBA from Wake Forest University and a bachelor’s of science in aeronautical/astronautical engineering at Ohio State University.
“I am very excited with Mr. Croskey’s addition to LSI’s executive team,” LSI CEO Dennis Wells said in the announcement. “The world of signage and graphics is changing rapidly and we need smart energetic people working to grow our share in this large addressable market. He and his team will work closely with Shawn Toney, president, LSI Lighting Segment, and John Bagwell, president, LSI Technology Segment, to grow LSI’s position as a leader in image solutions.”
Croskey will replace David McCauley, who served as the leader of the graphics segment for 18 years.
Cincinnati-based LSI uses technology, design and manufacturing to produce efficient, high-quality lighting and graphics products. The company has undergone a shuffling of its top executives in the past year, most notably with new CEO Dennis Wells taking over the role from Bob Ready sooner than originally projected.








 





 















































 



















